# Environment Variables for Production

## Backend (Render)
Set these environment variables in your Render dashboard:
- `SECRET_KEY`: A strong secret key for Django
- `DEBUG`: `False`
- `DATABASE_URL`: Your PostgreSQL database URL
- `ALLOWED_HOSTS`: Your Render domain (e.g., `your-app.onrender.com`)

## Frontend (Vercel)
Set this environment variable in your Vercel project settings:
- `VITE_API_URL`: Your backend URL (e.g., `https://your-backend.onrender.com`)

**IMPORTANT**: Without setting `VITE_API_URL` in Vercel, the frontend will try to connect to localhost and won't work in production!
